Vice President Yemi Osinbajo said the N-Power Graduate Skills Acquisition Programme will be expanded and made better to benefit more Nigerian youths, as he also announced that 20,000 youths will be trained in various skills across the country. Osinbajo spoke both in Abia and Enugu states, where he visited various skill training centres. In Abia, he visited Kiara De-Luke Multi-Skill and Entrepreneurship Centre, an N-Power training centre at Umuobiakwa in Obingwa LocalGovernment Area.